{"sectionId":671,"sectionIdLiteral":"671","humanId":"lesson-256","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"God is the only goal I have today.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 256"},"annotation":"W-256","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-256\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"671#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>The way to God is through forgiveness here.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>There is no other way.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>If sin had not been cherished by the mind, what need would there have been to find the way to where you are?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Who would still be uncertain?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Who could be unsure of who he is?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And who would yet remain asleep, in heavy clouds of doubt about the holiness of him whom God created sinless?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>Here we can but dream.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>But we can dream we have forgiven him in whom all sin remains impossible, and it is this we choose to dream today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#1:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>God is our goal; forgiveness is the means by which our minds return to Him at last.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"671#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>And so, our Father, would we come to You in Your appointed way.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"671#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>We have no goal except to hear Your Voice, and find the way Your sacred Word has pointed out to us.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"The way